reviews.review:
- So many characters with nothing much to contribute other than running around
- Lots of action and little character development
- Beautiful to look at and empty of meaning
- The cardinal sin of introducing clumsy baseless plot points in order to jam home an awkward ending

It's like the writers were a bunch of kids building a go-cart, just hammering on bits and pieces until it would more or less roll and then parking it next to the beautiful craft that WAS Star Wars, trying to imply it belongs. No problem if you're fanfic writers but come on, you're supposed to be professionals. If I were the Skywalkers, I'd demand they take my name off it. 

I don't expect to like everything in every movie but I never thought I'd walk out of a SW movie feeling so...meh.
Good conclusion to the saga. could've done without Palpatine and the nostalgia but the relationship and you intimacy of Rey and Ben was spot on
There are a few decent parts, but the plot is as disappointing as ep 8.
Very pleased J.J. righted the ship after the WORST JEDI. Movie had good flow from beginning to end. A lot of holes were filled in some left open. Overall a good ending to the series
A terrible end for a terrible trilogy, had some good moments of mostly fan service but the plot line like the rest of the Disney trilogy undermines the other star wars trilogy.

Beautiful story of redemption and facing your worst fears. A fitting and emotional end to the Skywalker legacy and one brimming with hope for the future of Star Wars. There are a lot of naysayers to the modern day Star Wars trilogy, but I encourage the viewers to take each film on its own individual merit and that viewpoint will open the story and allow the Star Wars universe to expand for you.

I enjoyed the movie, thought it was an exciting finish to the saga. Although I was turned off a bit at the beginning because it seemed like everything happening was sped up and I couldn't grasp where the film was supposed to start off from in the first place. A few surprises got my attention throughout the movie as well, and an overall rating I'd give is a 7/10
An amazing finish to the Skywalker Saga.
Great way to wrap up the series of films. A little sad to see it end.
